body:
Hey there,

I'm using instantsearch on a user search page and for some reason it's coming up with my 'items' index instead of my 'users' index. This screen was previously working, but I needed to edit it to remove redundant instances of `<InstantSearch>` that I had in the drawers, and move the main instance from just below `<View style={styles.container}>` to the top of the return as I'm doing on another similar screen. And now for some reason it won't load the correct index. Any ideas on this?

The indexName is only defined here `const currentIndex = "users"`, there are other instances of `<InstantSearch>` on other screens, but the only screen that uses the 'items' index is not loaded at this point in the app.

```
render() {
        const currentIndex = "users"
        const algoliaAppId = "******"
        const algoliaApiKey = "****"
        const sortUsers = ...        
        const DrawerHeader = ((props) => { ...})
	return (
	    <InstantSearch
	        appId={algoliaAppId}
	        apiKey={algoliaApiKey}
	        indexName={currentIndex}
				root={{
		      Root: View,
		      props: {
		        style: {
		          flex: 1
		        }
		      }
		    }}>
	        <Drawer 
	            type="overlay"
	            open={this.state.refineDrawerVisible}
	            openDrawerOffset={0.5}
	            closedDrawerOffset={0}
	            //panCloseMask={0.6}
	            //closedDrawerOffset={-3}
	            onCloseStart={() => {this.setState({refineDrawerVisible: false});}} 
	            tapToClose={true}
	            side={'right'} 
	            styles={drawerStyles}
	                tweenHandler={(ratio) => ({
	                main: { opacity:(2-ratio)/2 }
	            })}
	            content={
	            	<View>
	                    <DrawerHeader headerTitle={'Refine'} drawerVisible={'refineDrawerVisible'}/>
	                    <ScrollView>
	                        <DrawerCategories
	                            indexName={currentIndex}
	                            attributeName={'companyName'}
	                            header={'Company'}/>
	                        <Separator/>
	                    </ScrollView>
	                </View>
	            }>
	        <Drawer 
	            type="overlay"
	            open={this.state.sortDrawerVisible}
	            openDrawerOffset={0.5}
	            closedDrawerOffset={0}
	            //panCloseMask={0.6}
	            //closedDrawerOffset={-3}
	            onCloseStart={() => {this.setState({sortDrawerVisible: false});}}
	            tapToClose={true}
	            side={'right'} 
	            styles={drawerStyles}
	                tweenHandler={(ratio) => ({
	                main: { opacity:(2-ratio)/2 }
	            })}
	            content={
	            	<View>
	                    <DrawerHeader headerTitle={'Sort'} drawerVisible={'sortDrawerVisible'}/>
	                    <ScrollView>
	                        <DrawerSortBy
	                           indexName={currentIndex}
	                           sortItems={sortUsers}/>
	                    </ScrollView>
	                </View>
	            }>
			<View style={styles.container}>
	            <View style={{flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center'}}>
	                <SearchBox/>
	            </View>
	            <Separator/>
	            <CurrentRefinements/>
	            <Hits 
	                fieldOne="name"
	                fieldThree="companyName"
	                uid={this.user.uid}
	                navigation={this.props.navigation}
	                usersRef={this.usersRef}
	                chatsRef={this.chatsRef}
	                onPressHit={this.onPressHit}/>
				<ActionButton 
					useNativeFeedback={false}
					buttonColor={Colors.secondaryColor}
					icon={<Icon name="check" size={Styles.primaryIconSize} color={Colors.primaryGrayColor}/>}
					onPress={() => this.submit()}>
				</ActionButton>
			</View>
			</Drawer>
			</Drawer>
		</InstantSearch>
		);
}
```
